President Barack Obama has proclaimed March 2013 as Women's History Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of women's contributions to American society and the ongoing challenges they face, such as the gender pay gap and lack of workplace flexibility. The President also emphasizes his administration's efforts to address these issues, such as signing the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act and providing greater protections and preventive services for women under the Affordable Care Act. He encourages all Americans to observe Women's History Month and celebrate International Women's Day on March 8th.